[9] Spain
Date: Sat 17 Mar 2018
Source: Levante [in Spanish, trans. Mod.LK, edited]
http://www.levante-emv.com/comunitat-valenciana/2018/03/14/brote-sarampion-afecta-11-personas/1691117.html


Two unvaccinated minors with measles, admitted last February 2018 in the hospital of Manises, are the focus of the outbreak of the infectious disease [measles] that has been registered in the hospital center and that already affects 11 people, although the figure could increase to 16.

This was confirmed yesterday [16 Mar 2018] by sources of the Ministry of Health and the management of the hospital, which emphasized that "all preventive and control measures" dictated by the General Directorate of Public Health that intervened before the outbreak the past Fri 9 Mar 2018 had been done.

On that day, 9 Mar 2018, the infection of an employee who went to the ER on Thu [8 Mar 2018] with symptoms had been confirmed. Another worker had been discharged from the hospital (on Wed [7 Mar 2018]), and a 3rd employee had also come to the emergency room with the same symptoms, for which he was admitted.

There had been talk of 9 infected in the outbreak (4 workers and 5 neighbors), but the truth is that there are already 11 people affected, and 5 other cases are "under study," according to official health sources. ...-more

